&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview – Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;CAD Designer/Drafter&lt;/strong&gt; will be responsible for performing professional-level CAD services such as drafting of drawings in AutoCAD and amending Revit models, assessing and augmenting drawing sets against basic building code requirements. In this role you will be primarily augmenting various types of schematics and architectural drawings overlaying fire safety related information such as fire resistance rating of walls, floors, doors, exit sign locations, occupancy load calculations, separation of exits and similar, under the guidance and supervision of lead consultants and designers. The ideal candidate would have strong technical skills to produce detailed drawings and layouts for fire protection systems, including fire sprinklers, and special hazard suppression systems. The ideal candidate will have experience using AutoCAD and Revit and an understanding of relevant fire protection codes and standards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be based in Khobar, KSA and will be responsible for supporting projects across India and Overseas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role offers the chance to work in a fast-paced environment and advance your career within a supportive and diverse team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A verifiable and demonstrated knowledge of engineering principles or construction technology &amp;amp; practices would be the key requirement for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
